Global Neulasta (Pegfilgrastim) and Biosimilar Market Insights
Neulasta (Pegfilgrastim) and Biosimilar Market size was valued at USD 5.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 8.1 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.4% from 2024 to 2030.

Neulasta (Pegfilgrastim) and Biosimilar Market Overview
The global Neulasta (Pegfilgrastim) and biosimilar market has shown significant growth over the years, driven by increasing cancer prevalence and rising demand for affordable biologics. In 2024, the global market value for Neulasta and its biosimilars reached approximately USD 7.3 billion. As of 2025, the biosimilar market continues to expand rapidly, with a market value projected to surpass USD 3 billion, thanks to a growing shift towards cost-effective treatments. The market growth is also supported by continuous advancements in biotechnology and regulatory approvals of biosimilars that provide similar efficacy and safety to the original drug. The oncology sector remains the leading application area, accounting for the majority of market share in the global industry.

